[Amit Varma]: Wow, that's superb.

02:25:40.040 --> 02:25:44.040
[Amit Varma]: So, you know, one of the things sort of Chuck told me about you

02:25:44.040 --> 02:25:47.040
[Amit Varma]: is that from sort of being the brash, young upstart

02:25:47.040 --> 02:25:50.040
[Amit Varma]: in the late 90s, you are now like a senior citizen

02:25:50.040 --> 02:25:52.040
[Amit Varma]: of the Indian rock scene and so on and so forth.

02:25:52.040 --> 02:25:54.040
[Amit Varma]: Budda uncle.

02:25:54.040 --> 02:25:57.040
[Amit Varma]: Yeah, I was trying to be polite there.

02:25:57.040 --> 02:25:59.040
[Amit Varma]: Budda uncle.

02:25:59.040 --> 02:26:02.040
[Amit Varma]: Tell me, how has the scene kind of evolved

02:26:02.040 --> 02:26:03.040
[Amit Varma]: over all of this time?

02:26:03.040 --> 02:26:06.040
[Amit Varma]: Because whenever a new ecosystem emerges,

02:26:06.040 --> 02:26:09.040
[Amit Varma]: and, you know, in that period of time in the 90s,

02:26:09.040 --> 02:26:11.040
[Amit Varma]: ending at perhaps when Zero came around,

02:26:11.040 --> 02:26:13.040
[Amit Varma]: I was writing a lot for the Rock Street Journal

02:26:13.040 --> 02:26:15.040
[Amit Varma]: and I was into the scene.

02:26:15.040 --> 02:26:18.040
[Amit Varma]: And it seemed at that time that our bands

02:26:18.040 --> 02:26:20.040
[Amit Varma]: aren't really quite there yet.

02:26:20.040 --> 02:26:22.040
[Amit Varma]: Some stuff is derivative.

02:26:22.040 --> 02:26:23.040
[Amit Varma]: It's not that deep.

02:26:23.040 --> 02:26:25.040
[Amit Varma]: And obviously the way ecosystems evolve

02:26:25.040 --> 02:26:27.040
[Amit Varma]: is over a period of time as more and more people

02:26:27.040 --> 02:26:30.040
[Amit Varma]: come into it, as time passes, it gets deeper.

02:26:30.040 --> 02:26:33.040
[Amit Varma]: Just the overall quality gets better.

02:26:33.040 --> 02:26:36.040
[Amit Varma]: I mean, I kind of tuned out of the indie scene

02:26:36.040 --> 02:26:37.040
[Amit Varma]: around the time Hook came out.

02:26:37.040 --> 02:26:40.040
[Amit Varma]: And I remember at that time listening to that album

02:26:40.040 --> 02:26:42.040
[Amit Varma]: and thinking it is, and that's what I was telling Chuck

02:26:42.040 --> 02:26:45.040
[Amit Varma]: in the morning today, that it's just so much tighter

02:26:45.040 --> 02:26:47.040
[Amit Varma]: and crisper than a lot of the other stuff

02:26:47.040 --> 02:26:48.040
[Amit Varma]: that is coming out.

02:26:48.040 --> 02:26:51.040
[Amit Varma]: And absolutely no disrespect intended to, you know,

02:26:51.040 --> 02:26:54.040
[Amit Varma]: any of the other bands around that period.

02:26:54.040 --> 02:26:58.040
[Amit Varma]: So fill me into how that scene kind of evolved

02:26:58.040 --> 02:27:01.040
[Amit Varma]: because at the same time, the times are changing, right?

02:27:01.040 --> 02:27:06.040
[Amit Varma]: Things are opening up, the internet is exploding.

02:27:06.040 --> 02:27:11.040
[Amit Varma]: Where's sort of, is there like,

02:27:11.040 --> 02:27:14.040
[Amit Varma]: is there one thing you can call as an indie rock scene today

02:27:14.040 --> 02:27:16.040
[Amit Varma]: or is it just different things happening

02:27:16.040 --> 02:27:17.040
[Amit Varma]: all over the place?

02:27:17.040 --> 02:27:19.040
[Amit Varma]: For me and those of my listeners

02:27:19.040 --> 02:27:21.040
[Amit Varma]: who may not really have followed this,

02:27:21.040 --> 02:27:23.040
[Amit Varma]: just kind of fill me into what's happened.

02:27:23.040 --> 02:27:25.040
[Amit Varma]: What are the parts of it which kind of fill you

02:27:25.040 --> 02:27:27.040
[Amit Varma]: with happiness when you look at it and you say,

02:27:27.040 --> 02:27:29.040
[Amit Varma]: yeah, you know, things happen just right.

02:27:29.040 --> 02:27:32.040
[Amit Varma]: And where do you kind of feel disappointed

02:27:32.040 --> 02:27:35.040
[Amit Varma]: or let down and so on?

02:27:35.040 --> 02:27:38.040
[Guest]: Well, I've seen it like transition at least three or four,

02:27:38.040 --> 02:27:40.040
[Guest]: maybe five or six times.

02:27:40.040 --> 02:27:47.040
[Guest]: So like when I was just getting into playing music,

02:27:47.040 --> 02:27:49.040
[Guest]: I think probably the biggest band in the country

02:27:49.040 --> 02:27:50.040
[Guest]: at the time was Indus Creed.

02:27:50.040 --> 02:27:53.040
[Guest]: Now we had Star TV and we could see their videos on Star TV.

02:27:53.040 --> 02:27:56.040
[Guest]: So in terms of that reach,

02:27:56.040 --> 02:28:00.040
[Guest]: I don't think it's ever been as good since then.

02:28:00.040 --> 02:28:03.040
[Guest]: Then you had bands like Pentagram putting out albums

02:28:03.040 --> 02:28:07.040
[Guest]: of original music, which kind of inspired us to do the same.

02:28:07.040 --> 02:28:10.040
[Guest]: Now when we put out that first album,

02:28:10.040 --> 02:28:14.040
[Guest]: which we recorded in a balcony on a computer,

02:28:14.040 --> 02:28:15.040
[Guest]: which was to keep overheating,

02:28:15.040 --> 02:28:17.040
[Guest]: just getting into the technology

02:28:17.040 --> 02:28:19.040
[Guest]: where we were able to do it ourselves.

02:28:19.040 --> 02:28:20.040
[Guest]: That was the whole thing.

02:28:20.040 --> 02:28:23.040
[Guest]: We had creative control and for whatever reason,

02:28:23.040 --> 02:28:26.040
[Guest]: you could put the blame squarely on us for how that sounds.

02:28:26.040 --> 02:28:28.040
[Guest]: But at least it was ours.

02:28:28.040 --> 02:28:29.040
[Guest]: We were like in total control.

02:28:29.040 --> 02:28:31.040
[Guest]: There was no one paying us money and saying,

02:28:31.040 --> 02:28:33.040
[Guest]: we want this, we want that.

02:28:33.040 --> 02:28:35.040
[Guest]: Nothing of that was part of the process.

02:28:35.040 --> 02:28:39.040
[Guest]: So there's always been artists in any country

02:28:39.040 --> 02:28:41.040
[Guest]: that are still doing that

02:28:41.040 --> 02:28:43.040
[Guest]: and were able to do it at that time.

02:28:43.040 --> 02:28:45.040
[Guest]: If your dad owned a studio, for example,

02:28:45.040 --> 02:28:48.040
[Guest]: then you could do that thing in the 80s.

02:28:48.040 --> 02:28:53.040
[Guest]: The technology became a bit more democratic.

02:28:53.040 --> 02:28:56.040
[Guest]: Now the downside to that is now everyone can do it.

02:28:56.040 --> 02:28:58.040
[Guest]: So where do you put a distinction

02:28:58.040 --> 02:29:00.040
[Guest]: in between a bona fide artist and some guy

02:29:00.040 --> 02:29:02.040
[Guest]: who's just playing around in a garage band

02:29:02.040 --> 02:29:05.040
[Guest]: and came up with some groove that he liked,

02:29:05.040 --> 02:29:07.040
[Guest]: put on some other loop and put some vibes.

02:29:07.040 --> 02:29:09.040
[Guest]: The moment that loop-based thing started happening,

02:29:09.040 --> 02:29:11.040
[Guest]: I noticed it became like,

02:29:11.040 --> 02:29:14.040
[Guest]: now it's not just the realm of musicians.

02:29:14.040 --> 02:29:17.040
[Guest]: Now anyone with some taste and hopefully some taste

02:29:17.040 --> 02:29:20.040
[Guest]: and some technology can put the two together

02:29:20.040 --> 02:29:23.040
[Guest]: and come up with something.

02:29:23.040 --> 02:29:29.040
[Guest]: And once people start liking that,

02:29:29.040 --> 02:29:31.040
[Guest]: the thing is, as long as there are people to listen to it,

02:29:31.040 --> 02:29:34.040
[Guest]: you can't say that it's not legit or whatever.

02:29:34.040 --> 02:29:35.040
[Guest]: As long as there are people listening to it

02:29:35.040 --> 02:29:36.040
[Guest]: and having an honest reaction,

02:29:36.040 --> 02:29:40.040
[Guest]: I think that's, for me, the parameters of legit.

02:29:40.040 --> 02:29:42.040
[Guest]: Whatever it is.

02:29:42.040 --> 02:29:45.040
[Guest]: You can have spoken word over some concert piano.

02:29:45.040 --> 02:29:48.040
[Guest]: Someone digs it, great.

02:29:48.040 --> 02:29:51.040
[Guest]: Who's to say this is good?

02:29:51.040 --> 02:29:56.040
[Guest]: For example, like a kid.

02:29:56.040 --> 02:29:58.040
[Guest]: My daughter, she listens to stuff.

02:29:58.040 --> 02:29:59.040
[Guest]: She doesn't have those parameters

02:29:59.040 --> 02:30:00.040
[Guest]: about this is good, this is bad.

02:30:00.040 --> 02:30:02.040
[Guest]: You either like it or you don't like it.

02:30:02.040 --> 02:30:05.040
[Guest]: So that's as honest a reaction as you're going to get.

02:30:05.040 --> 02:30:08.040
[Guest]: So there'll always be that,

02:30:08.040 --> 02:30:11.040
[Guest]: whatever music is coming out.

02:30:11.040 --> 02:30:16.040
[Guest]: In terms of the scene itself, how it grows.

02:30:16.040 --> 02:30:19.040
[Guest]: When I was in New Zealand, initially from 2004,

02:30:19.040 --> 02:30:22.040
[Guest]: I think that time was the biggest boom.

02:30:22.040 --> 02:30:24.040
[Guest]: I felt like I missed out on a bit of that.

02:30:24.040 --> 02:30:26.040
[Guest]: And when I came back in 2009,

02:30:26.040 --> 02:30:29.040
[Guest]: I kind of caught the last bit of it.

02:30:29.040 --> 02:30:35.040
[Guest]: So down to the first N87 festival to 2010 or 2011.

02:30:35.040 --> 02:30:36.040
[Unknown]: I don't know.

02:30:36.040 --> 02:30:37.040
[Unknown]: 2010.

02:30:37.040 --> 02:30:38.040
[Unknown]: 2010, yeah.

02:30:38.040 --> 02:30:40.040
[Guest]: So that was a totally cool vibe

02:30:40.040 --> 02:30:43.040
[Guest]: and it was no big, huge thing

02:30:43.040 --> 02:30:46.040
[Guest]: which everyone and their friend came along to.

02:30:46.040 --> 02:30:48.040
[Guest]: It was just basically artists and people

02:30:48.040 --> 02:30:50.040
[Guest]: who knew that this was happening,

02:30:50.040 --> 02:30:52.040
[Guest]: landed up in Pune and it was a beautiful time.

02:30:52.040 --> 02:30:54.040
[Guest]: So the first couple of years,

02:30:54.040 --> 02:30:57.040
[Guest]: then it started getting bigger and bigger.

02:30:57.040 --> 02:30:58.040
[Guest]: And then with every scene,

02:30:58.040 --> 02:31:00.040
[Guest]: there'll be one upwards trajectory

02:31:00.040 --> 02:31:01.040
[Guest]: and then there's one downwards trajectory.

02:31:01.040 --> 02:31:04.040
[Guest]: And again, something else will come along and take that.

02:31:04.040 --> 02:31:08.040
[Guest]: And that's the whole thing about indie versus Bollywood.

02:31:08.040 --> 02:31:10.040
[Guest]: Now, the moment anything becomes big,

02:31:10.040 --> 02:31:13.040
[Guest]: Bollywood absorbs it and pulls it in

02:31:13.040 --> 02:31:14.040
[Guest]: because Bollywood has money

02:31:14.040 --> 02:31:16.040
[Guest]: and Bollywood can get whatever it wants.

02:31:16.040 --> 02:31:17.040
[Guest]: You're not going to say like,

02:31:17.040 --> 02:31:20.040
[Guest]: no, don't pay me too close to make this song.

02:31:20.040 --> 02:31:21.040
[Guest]: Pay me that money.

02:31:21.040 --> 02:31:22.040
[Guest]: I'll do whatever you want.

02:31:22.040 --> 02:31:25.040
[Guest]: You'll take it at least somewhat financially secure

02:31:25.040 --> 02:31:28.040
[Guest]: and then you do what you want to apart from that.

02:31:28.040 --> 02:31:32.040
[Guest]: So I guess the whole idea is like,

02:31:32.040 --> 02:31:35.040
[Guest]: still now, the biggest songwriters in India

02:31:35.040 --> 02:31:37.040
[Guest]: still don't get to control their own music.

02:31:37.040 --> 02:31:39.040
[Guest]: I think that's the saddest part.

02:31:39.040 --> 02:31:40.040
[Guest]: I know music directors

02:31:40.040 --> 02:31:43.040
[Guest]: who didn't get permission to play their own songs.

02:31:43.040 --> 02:31:44.040
[Guest]: Can you believe that?

02:31:44.040 --> 02:31:47.040
[Guest]: For me, that was like a travesty of justice.

02:31:47.040 --> 02:31:48.040
[Guest]: Why do you...

02:31:48.040 --> 02:31:50.040
[Guest]: Because some other company owned it

02:31:50.040 --> 02:31:52.040
[Guest]: and you know how the things get in the industry.

02:31:52.040 --> 02:31:55.040
[Guest]: It's not as rosy as it seems.

02:31:55.040 --> 02:31:57.040
[Guest]: People who control the money,

02:31:57.040 --> 02:32:00.040
[Guest]: they want to obviously control their investment

02:32:00.040 --> 02:32:01.040
[Guest]: and they'll do whatever they have to do

02:32:01.040 --> 02:32:04.040
[Guest]: to make sure that they retain that power.

02:32:04.040 --> 02:32:07.040
[Guest]: So until I guess, you know,

02:32:07.040 --> 02:32:09.040
[Guest]: mainstream artists are able to...

02:32:09.040 --> 02:32:10.040
[Guest]: I mean, you look at India,

02:32:10.040 --> 02:32:11.040
[Guest]: it's kind of an anomaly in a sense

02:32:11.040 --> 02:32:14.040
[Guest]: because I think no other country does film music

02:32:14.040 --> 02:32:17.040
[Guest]: take such a dominant part of the mainstream music culture.

02:32:17.040 --> 02:32:20.040
[Guest]: It's like we have fed music with images

02:32:20.040 --> 02:32:22.040
[Guest]: from a time immemorial,

02:32:22.040 --> 02:32:24.040
[Guest]: since, you know, 60s or whatever.

02:32:24.040 --> 02:32:28.040
[Guest]: So like we had MTE before there was MTE in India.

02:32:28.040 --> 02:32:31.040
[Guest]: So, you know,

02:32:31.040 --> 02:32:35.040
[Guest]: it's always going to have some kind of a thing.

02:32:35.040 --> 02:32:37.040
[Guest]: And then now as the mainstream changes,

02:32:37.040 --> 02:32:39.040
[Guest]: like saying from Bollywood to now Netflix

02:32:39.040 --> 02:32:40.040
[Guest]: and all that is coming out,

02:32:40.040 --> 02:32:42.040
[Guest]: then there's like, oh, this also exists.

02:32:42.040 --> 02:32:44.040
[Guest]: And then the lines start blurring, you know,

02:32:44.040 --> 02:32:46.040
[Guest]: between Indie and mainstream.

02:32:46.040 --> 02:32:50.040
[Guest]: So many of the artists that you would classify as Indie artists

02:32:50.040 --> 02:32:51.040
[Guest]: have got links.

02:32:51.040 --> 02:32:53.040
[Guest]: I mean, even down to me having played on,

02:32:53.040 --> 02:32:56.040
[Guest]: you know, heaps of Bollywood songs.

02:32:56.040 --> 02:32:58.040
[Guest]: You know, and for me, initially,

02:32:58.040 --> 02:33:00.040
[Guest]: it was like a bit of like, you know,

02:33:00.040 --> 02:33:03.040
[Guest]: I only want to play on good music.

02:33:03.040 --> 02:33:04.040
[Guest]: I don't want to play on shit.

02:33:04.040 --> 02:33:06.040
[Guest]: But then it became like, you know,

02:33:06.040 --> 02:33:08.040
[Guest]: let's bring the best that we can

02:33:08.040 --> 02:33:10.040
[Guest]: to whatever it is that we are given today.

02:33:10.040 --> 02:33:11.040
[Guest]: It became like a challenge.

02:33:11.040 --> 02:33:13.040
[Guest]: You know, what can you do with this?

02:33:13.040 --> 02:33:15.040
[Guest]: What can you turn it into?

02:33:15.040 --> 02:33:17.040
[Guest]: So that is what I got off on.

02:33:17.040 --> 02:33:19.040
[Guest]: So as long as, you know, there was that,

02:33:19.040 --> 02:33:21.040
[Guest]: I still found it challenging.

02:33:21.040 --> 02:33:23.040
[Guest]: Like you never knew what you were going to get,

02:33:23.040 --> 02:33:24.040
[Guest]: you know, in that sense.

02:33:24.040 --> 02:33:25.040
[Guest]: And then you suddenly like,

02:33:25.040 --> 02:33:28.040
[Guest]: okay, come up with a killer hook now, right now.

02:33:28.040 --> 02:33:29.040
[Guest]: What do you do?

02:33:29.040 --> 02:33:30.040
[Guest]: You know, it's like,

02:33:30.040 --> 02:33:31.040
[Guest]: you either have the goods or you don't.

02:33:31.040 --> 02:33:32.040
[Guest]: So in that sense, it was like,

02:33:32.040 --> 02:33:35.040
[Guest]: it still kind of separated the, you know,

02:33:35.040 --> 02:33:37.040
[Guest]: the men from the boys, as it were.

02:33:37.040 --> 02:33:40.040
[Guest]: So like, there's still killer musicianship in Bollywood.

02:33:40.040 --> 02:33:43.040
[Guest]: Like you see some of those Indian classical guys do.

02:33:43.040 --> 02:33:44.040
[Guest]: Like, there's like not,

02:33:44.040 --> 02:33:46.040
[Guest]: I live to live five lifetimes for me

02:33:46.040 --> 02:33:48.040
[Guest]: to get that good and how they go.

02:33:48.040 --> 02:33:49.040
[Guest]: And they just close their eyes and they do it,

02:33:49.040 --> 02:33:51.040
[Guest]: you know, just like, you know.

02:33:51.040 --> 02:33:53.040
[Guest]: Because there's years and years and years of practice

02:33:53.040 --> 02:33:55.040
[Guest]: which has to go into that tradition for them

02:33:55.040 --> 02:33:58.040
[Guest]: to be able to even consider a good musician.

02:33:58.040 --> 02:34:00.040
[Guest]: You know, it's like you pick up a guitar

02:34:00.040 --> 02:34:01.040
[Guest]: and you learn three chords and,

02:34:01.040 --> 02:34:03.040
[Guest]: bro, I've written my own song, you know.

02:34:03.040 --> 02:34:06.040
[Guest]: So it's a different world in that sense.

02:34:06.040 --> 02:34:09.040
[Guest]: But I've always had respect for good musicianship

02:34:09.040 --> 02:34:10.040
[Guest]: in any genre.

02:34:10.040 --> 02:34:12.040
[Guest]: You know, you can always sense that,

02:34:12.040 --> 02:34:15.040
[Guest]: okay, this guy is a motherfucker at what he does.

02:34:15.040 --> 02:34:17.040
[Guest]: You know, there's like a jazz saying,

02:34:17.040 --> 02:34:19.040
[Guest]: like the best guys are called that.

02:34:19.040 --> 02:34:21.040
[Guest]: So it's like,

02:34:21.040 --> 02:34:24.040
[Guest]: you have to have respect for that sort of thing

02:34:24.040 --> 02:34:25.040
[Guest]: in that sense.

02:34:25.040 --> 02:34:28.040
[Guest]: You know, the lines will, you know,

02:34:28.040 --> 02:34:29.040
[Guest]: keep blurring

02:34:29.040 --> 02:34:32.040
[Guest]: because that cross-pollination will keep happening.

02:34:32.040 --> 02:34:35.040
[Guest]: And who's basically controlling the money

02:34:35.040 --> 02:34:38.040
[Guest]: will ultimately control what's going in the mainstream.

02:34:38.040 --> 02:34:39.040
[Guest]: You know, it just depends.

02:34:39.040 --> 02:34:41.040
[Guest]: I mean, Netflix has got a budget.

02:34:41.040 --> 02:34:42.040
[Guest]: Bro, there you go.

02:34:42.040 --> 02:34:43.040
[Guest]: Bollywood's got a budget.

02:34:43.040 --> 02:34:44.040
[Guest]: Bro, there you go.

02:34:44.040 --> 02:34:46.040
[Guest]: It's just like, who's going to pay me to do this?

02:34:48.040 --> 02:34:49.040
[Unknown]: That was fascinating.

02:34:49.040 --> 02:34:50.040
[Unknown]: I mean, I know you have a question, Amit,

02:34:50.040 --> 02:34:52.040
[Unknown]: but I just wanted to close that out with an observation.

02:34:52.040 --> 02:34:54.040
[Unknown]: I think, Warren, you're the only person I know

02:34:54.040 --> 02:34:57.040
[Unknown]: who's actually played at each stage at NH7 Weekender.

02:34:57.040 --> 02:35:00.040
[Unknown]: The rock and metal stage, the alternative stage,

02:35:00.040 --> 02:35:01.040
[Unknown]: the folk stage, obviously,

02:35:01.040 --> 02:35:03.040
[Unknown]: and also the electronic stage.

02:35:03.040 --> 02:35:04.040
[Unknown]: I think I've seen you once.

02:35:04.040 --> 02:35:06.040
[Guest]: No, there's two other people who have done it.

02:35:06.040 --> 02:35:08.040
[Guest]: There's Sid Couto and Sid Busserud.

02:35:08.040 --> 02:35:09.040
[Guest]: Both the Sids.

02:35:09.040 --> 02:35:10.040
[Unknown]: Fair enough.

02:35:10.040 --> 02:35:11.040
[Unknown]: All right, fair enough.

02:35:11.040 --> 02:35:12.040
[Unknown]: The first then.

02:35:12.040 --> 02:35:13.040
[Unknown]: Let's call it the first.

02:35:13.040 --> 02:35:15.040
[Unknown]: Sorry, that is just an observation

02:35:15.040 --> 02:35:16.040
[Unknown]: I wanted to get out of the way.

02:35:16.040 --> 02:35:20.040
[Amit Varma]: No, no, and that's a kind of a telling observation.

02:35:20.040 --> 02:35:22.040
[Amit Varma]: So when you kind of look ahead,

02:35:22.040 --> 02:35:24.040
[Amit Varma]: like what you've done over the last 10, 15 years

02:35:24.040 --> 02:35:27.040
[Amit Varma]: is you've done work that pays the bills, right?

02:35:27.040 --> 02:35:29.040
[Amit Varma]: Sessions work, your Bollywood work, whatever.

02:35:29.040 --> 02:35:30.040
[Amit Varma]: It pays the bills.

02:35:30.040 --> 02:35:31.040
[Amit Varma]: You got to do it.

02:35:31.040 --> 02:35:32.040
[Amit Varma]: That's an imperative.

02:35:32.040 --> 02:35:34.040
[Amit Varma]: At the same time, you've done the stuff that you love.

02:35:34.040 --> 02:35:37.040
[Amit Varma]: How do you see things going forward?

02:35:37.040 --> 02:35:38.040
[Amit Varma]: Is that also drudgery?

02:35:38.040 --> 02:35:39.040
[Amit Varma]: Because it is also music.

02:35:39.040 --> 02:35:40.040
[Amit Varma]: So is that also drudgery?

02:35:40.040 --> 02:35:42.040
[Amit Varma]: Or with what kind of attitude

02:35:42.040 --> 02:35:44.040
[Amit Varma]: or approach do you go into it?

02:35:44.040 --> 02:35:47.040
[Amit Varma]: You know, is some of that also work that you're proud of?

02:35:47.040 --> 02:35:49.040
[Amit Varma]: Or it's just something that you do to pay the bills

02:35:49.040 --> 02:35:51.040
[Guest]: and you got to do what you got to do?

02:35:51.040 --> 02:35:53.040
[Guest]: My attitude is very simple.

02:35:53.040 --> 02:35:56.040
[Guest]: I get paid to play guitar, and that's a blessing.

02:35:56.040 --> 02:35:58.040
[Guest]: I will never discount that enough.

02:35:58.040 --> 02:36:00.040
[Guest]: As long as I'm playing guitar,

02:36:00.040 --> 02:36:02.040
[Guest]: it doesn't really matter in that sense.

02:36:02.040 --> 02:36:04.040
[Guest]: You have to always come back to it.

02:36:04.040 --> 02:36:07.040
[Guest]: Because even on gigs, which I wasn't really enjoying,

02:36:07.040 --> 02:36:09.040
[Guest]: there were things that I would appreciate.

02:36:09.040 --> 02:36:12.040
[Guest]: Like the other musicians, you would have a hang after the gig.

02:36:12.040 --> 02:36:14.040
[Guest]: You may make connections, that sort of thing.

02:36:14.040 --> 02:36:17.040
[Guest]: Then sometimes the shared misery brings you together.

02:36:17.040 --> 02:36:21.040
[Guest]: So that happens as well.

02:36:21.040 --> 02:36:23.040
[Guest]: In fact, the thing which I did not really like

02:36:23.040 --> 02:36:25.040
[Guest]: about the whole commercial thing was mainly

02:36:25.040 --> 02:36:28.040
[Guest]: the whole drudgery of traveling and the early morning flights.

02:36:28.040 --> 02:36:29.040
[Guest]: It was brutal.

02:36:29.040 --> 02:36:31.040
[Guest]: I mean, every musician has to deal with it.

02:36:31.040 --> 02:36:34.040
[Guest]: So I'm the last person to complain.

02:36:34.040 --> 02:36:37.040
[Guest]: But it can take a toll on your system.

02:36:37.040 --> 02:36:40.040
[Guest]: I don't know how people can actually do tours

02:36:40.040 --> 02:36:42.040
[Guest]: for months and months without going home.

02:36:42.040 --> 02:36:46.040
[Guest]: We were banging out maximum three gigs on the weekend.

02:36:46.040 --> 02:36:48.040
[Guest]: When we would come home to family,

02:36:48.040 --> 02:36:49.040
[Guest]: at least on a Monday, Tuesday,

02:36:49.040 --> 02:36:52.040
[Guest]: we would see their faces before we took off again.

02:36:52.040 --> 02:36:54.040
[Guest]: But that whole thing about being away from home

02:36:54.040 --> 02:36:55.040
[Guest]: for a very long time, man,

02:36:55.040 --> 02:36:58.040
[Guest]: I have the ultimate respect for people who actually do that.

02:36:58.040 --> 02:37:01.040
[Guest]: And now with this virus thing,

02:37:01.040 --> 02:37:05.040
[Guest]: the whole life thing again is up in air.

02:37:05.040 --> 02:37:06.040
[Guest]: Because the moment things start opening,

02:37:06.040 --> 02:37:07.040
[Guest]: then something else happens,

02:37:07.040 --> 02:37:09.040
[Guest]: and then everything's closed again.

02:37:09.040 --> 02:37:11.040
[Guest]: Same thing happened in New Zealand.

02:37:11.040 --> 02:37:15.040
[Guest]: The biggest artists, they had a nice run till Jan.

02:37:15.040 --> 02:37:17.040
[Guest]: And then that Omicron thing happened,

02:37:17.040 --> 02:37:20.040
[Guest]: and everything is shut.

02:37:20.040 --> 02:37:21.040
[Guest]: Also, being a musician,

02:37:21.040 --> 02:37:22.040
[Guest]: you have to keep in mind

02:37:22.040 --> 02:37:24.040
[Guest]: that a lot of your income was seasonal.

02:37:24.040 --> 02:37:26.040
[Guest]: There'll be times of the year

02:37:26.040 --> 02:37:28.040
[Guest]: where you would make a lot of money,

02:37:28.040 --> 02:37:29.040
[Guest]: and then there were times of the year

02:37:29.040 --> 02:37:30.040
[Guest]: where nothing would come.

02:37:30.040 --> 02:37:32.040
[Guest]: So then you have to keep in mind

02:37:32.040 --> 02:37:34.040
[Guest]: that all that money that I've stashed up from that

02:37:34.040 --> 02:37:36.040
[Guest]: is going to cover you for the rest of the year,

02:37:36.040 --> 02:37:38.040
[Guest]: all that sort of thing.

02:37:38.040 --> 02:37:42.040
[Guest]: So you just have to be adaptable, man.

02:37:42.040 --> 02:37:44.040
[Guest]: Now I'm kind of putting my energy

02:37:44.040 --> 02:37:46.040
[Guest]: into at least doing a YouTube thing

02:37:46.040 --> 02:37:48.040
[Guest]: and seeing what happens there.

02:37:48.040 --> 02:37:50.040
[Guest]: Just do as many different things as possible.

02:37:50.040 --> 02:37:51.040
[Guest]: Because for a long time,

02:37:51.040 --> 02:37:53.040
[Guest]: it was just like I focused all my energy on Instagram.

02:37:53.040 --> 02:37:54.040
[Guest]: And then I was like,

02:37:54.040 --> 02:37:57.040
[Guest]: no, I can't really do only that.

02:37:57.040 --> 02:37:59.040
[Guest]: With this whole metaverse looming and everything,

02:37:59.040 --> 02:38:02.040
[Guest]: I don't really know how long I'm going to be on Instagram.

02:38:02.040 --> 02:38:06.040
[Guest]: Maybe things will change in five years or whatever.

02:38:06.040 --> 02:38:08.040
[Guest]: Remember, what was that thing that used to be there?

02:38:08.040 --> 02:38:10.040
[Guest]: Orkut.

02:38:10.040 --> 02:38:14.040
[Guest]: And before that, there was some MySpace.

02:38:14.040 --> 02:38:17.040
[Guest]: Man, there were so many musicians

02:38:17.040 --> 02:38:19.040
[Guest]: who invested a lot of time in MySpace.

02:38:19.040 --> 02:38:21.040
[Guest]: And then when MySpace went bust,

02:38:21.040 --> 02:38:23.040
[Guest]: they kind of got disillusioned,

02:38:23.040 --> 02:38:25.040
[Guest]: and then they said bye to social media.

02:38:25.040 --> 02:38:28.040
[Guest]: So now, I don't know if I should make a TikTok.

02:38:28.040 --> 02:38:30.040
[Guest]: In fact, I have made a TikTok account,

02:38:30.040 --> 02:38:34.040
[Guest]: but I think I posted only one video.

02:38:34.040 --> 02:38:37.040
[Guest]: I'm still learning about this algorithm and everything,

02:38:37.040 --> 02:38:38.040
[Guest]: like how it works,

02:38:38.040 --> 02:38:41.040
[Guest]: and post at certain times of the day and all that shit.

02:38:41.040 --> 02:38:43.040
[Guest]: And sometimes I just want to say,

02:38:43.040 --> 02:38:45.040
[Guest]: F it, you take it, you listen to it.

02:38:45.040 --> 02:38:47.040
[Guest]: Now, my job is over.

02:38:47.040 --> 02:38:51.040
[Guest]: Your job has begun.

02:38:51.040 --> 02:38:54.040
[Amit Varma]: Well, I've actually been enjoying your Instagram account

02:38:54.040 --> 02:38:55.040
[Amit Varma]: in the sense of,

02:38:55.040 --> 02:38:58.040
[Amit Varma]: it's just these little nuggets of happiness

02:38:58.040 --> 02:39:00.040
[Amit Varma]: that just keep coming when you play all these covers.

02:39:00.040 --> 02:39:02.040
[Guest]: I really enjoy that.

02:39:02.040 --> 02:39:04.040
[Guest]: I try to keep those live things now

02:39:04.040 --> 02:39:06.040
[Guest]: just as a temporary thing,

02:39:06.040 --> 02:39:08.040
[Guest]: because then I can...

02:39:08.040 --> 02:39:10.040
[Guest]: Early on, they used to save the chat.

02:39:10.040 --> 02:39:13.040
[Guest]: And I don't know if you've been on any of the Instagram live things.

02:39:13.040 --> 02:39:16.040
[Guest]: Sometimes there's some weird things that are in the chat,

02:39:16.040 --> 02:39:17.040
[Guest]: which I react to.

02:39:17.040 --> 02:39:18.040
[Guest]: And when that's taken away,

02:39:18.040 --> 02:39:20.040
[Guest]: you just think I'm talking rubbish.

02:39:20.040 --> 02:39:22.040
[Guest]: What's this guy on about?

02:39:22.040 --> 02:39:25.040
[Guest]: So I tend not to save them anymore.

02:39:25.040 --> 02:39:28.040
[Guest]: I think a couple of good ones are saved

02:39:28.040 --> 02:39:30.040
[Guest]: just to see what it was like.

02:39:30.040 --> 02:39:32.040
[Guest]: But apart from that,

02:39:32.040 --> 02:39:35.040
[Guest]: I don't really have a fixed time where I jump on it,

02:39:35.040 --> 02:39:38.040
[Guest]: because I know I could have a wider reach if I did that.

02:39:38.040 --> 02:39:41.040
[Guest]: But to me, it kind of feels more authentic if I just...

02:39:41.040 --> 02:39:42.040
[Guest]: I'm feeling it sometimes.

02:39:42.040 --> 02:39:44.040
[Guest]: I just feel like playing.

02:39:44.040 --> 02:39:45.040
[Guest]: I feel like seeing,

02:39:45.040 --> 02:39:46.040
[Guest]: okay, what do you want me to play?

02:39:46.040 --> 02:39:47.040
[Guest]: Okay, I'll play that.

02:39:47.040 --> 02:39:50.040
[Guest]: And sometimes I don't want to play requests.

02:39:50.040 --> 02:39:51.040
[Guest]: I was like,

02:39:51.040 --> 02:39:53.040
[Guest]: shut up and just let me do what I want to do right now.

02:39:53.040 --> 02:39:55.040
[Guest]: So it's kind of hard to say that

02:39:55.040 --> 02:39:58.040
[Guest]: without being deemed arrogant or impolite.

02:39:58.040 --> 02:40:00.040
[Guest]: But sometimes I have a better idea

02:40:00.040 --> 02:40:02.040
[Guest]: of what would be good to play right now.

02:40:02.040 --> 02:40:04.040
[Guest]: So just leave it to the DJ.

02:40:04.040 --> 02:40:06.040
[Guest]: You know, I'm the DJ right now.

02:40:06.040 --> 02:40:07.040
[Guest]: So let me do it.

02:40:07.040 --> 02:40:08.040
[Guest]: And sometimes I'm totally open, man.

02:40:08.040 --> 02:40:09.040
[Guest]: What do you want me to play?

02:40:09.040 --> 02:40:10.040
[Guest]: You want me to play some bapsa?

02:40:10.040 --> 02:40:11.040
[Guest]: Okay, here you go.

02:40:11.040 --> 02:40:13.040
[Guest]: Because it just depends what mood you're in.

02:40:13.040 --> 02:40:16.040
[Guest]: So it's kind of cool that way.

02:40:16.040 --> 02:40:20.040
[Guest]: And in terms of posting regular stuff,

02:40:20.040 --> 02:40:22.040
[Guest]: again, it's something I'm horrible at.

02:40:22.040 --> 02:40:25.040
[Guest]: I don't really have scheduled posts or anything like that.

02:40:25.040 --> 02:40:27.040
[Guest]: If I'm feeling up to it,

02:40:27.040 --> 02:40:31.040
[Guest]: I try to remain as authentic as possible to myself.

02:40:31.040 --> 02:40:33.040
[Guest]: The moment that goes away,

02:40:33.040 --> 02:40:35.040
[Guest]: then for me, it becomes like,

02:40:35.040 --> 02:40:37.040
[Unknown]: why am I doing this?

02:40:37.040 --> 02:40:38.040
[Unknown]: No, 100%.

02:40:38.040 --> 02:40:40.040
[Unknown]: I was about to just put that word in.

02:40:40.040 --> 02:40:42.040
[Unknown]: I think the coolest thing about your account

02:40:42.040 --> 02:40:43.040
[Unknown]: is the authenticity.

02:40:43.040 --> 02:40:45.040
[Unknown]: The fact that it's not planned.

02:40:45.040 --> 02:40:48.040
[Unknown]: It's like you don't have scheduled stuff that happens.

02:40:48.040 --> 02:40:50.040
[Unknown]: You know that this stuff is going to happen.

02:40:50.040 --> 02:40:51.040
[Unknown]: You'll do a live once in a while.

02:40:51.040 --> 02:40:52.040
[Unknown]: You'll do this.

02:40:52.040 --> 02:40:53.040
[Unknown]: You'll do that.

02:40:53.040 --> 02:40:55.040
[Unknown]: And it just makes it feel more human.

02:40:55.040 --> 02:40:59.040
[Guest]: I feel guilty promoting my own gigs on Instagram.

02:40:59.040 --> 02:41:01.040
[Unknown]: And that's as authentic as it gets.

02:41:01.040 --> 02:41:03.040
[Guest]: Putting more than one post about a gig.

02:41:03.040 --> 02:41:05.040
[Guest]: I was like, I posted it.

02:41:05.040 --> 02:41:09.040
[Guest]: I don't want to keep talking about the same thing.

02:41:11.040 --> 02:41:13.040
[Amit Varma]: So tell me something.

02:41:13.040 --> 02:41:15.040
[Amit Varma]: When we are young, for most people,

02:41:15.040 --> 02:41:17.040
[Amit Varma]: when we are young, we have goals.

02:41:17.040 --> 02:41:18.040
[Amit Varma]: I want to do this.

02:41:18.040 --> 02:41:19.040
[Amit Varma]: I want to do that.

02:41:19.040 --> 02:41:21.040
[Amit Varma]: You know, so on and so forth.

02:41:21.040 --> 02:41:23.040
[Amit Varma]: As you grow older, you realize that those goals are pointless.

02:41:23.040 --> 02:41:24.040
[Amit Varma]: They keep evolving anyway.

02:41:24.040 --> 02:41:25.040
[Amit Varma]: Many of them don't happen.

02:41:25.040 --> 02:41:27.040
[Amit Varma]: Many of your dreams are not going to come true.

02:41:27.040 --> 02:41:28.040
[Amit Varma]: You kind of figure it out.

02:41:28.040 --> 02:41:32.040
[Amit Varma]: And you figure out that the path to both excellence and happiness

02:41:32.040 --> 02:41:36.040
[Amit Varma]: lies not in achieving goals, but in just setting up processes.

02:41:36.040 --> 02:41:39.040
[Amit Varma]: Living your life in ways that make you happy.

02:41:39.040 --> 02:41:41.040
[Amit Varma]: Taking happiness in those small joys.

02:41:41.040 --> 02:41:42.040
[Amit Varma]: You know, you wake up in the morning and

02:41:42.040 --> 02:41:45.040
[Amit Varma]: I assume for you, if you wake up in the morning

02:41:45.040 --> 02:41:47.040
[Amit Varma]: and you know you're just going to play around with your guitar

02:41:47.040 --> 02:41:48.040
[Amit Varma]: and record something and blah blah.

02:41:48.040 --> 02:41:50.040
[Amit Varma]: You're already feeling happy at the start of the day

02:41:50.040 --> 02:41:52.040
[Amit Varma]: because that's what you want to do.

02:41:52.040 --> 02:41:53.040
[Amit Varma]: The goal may not matter.

02:41:53.040 --> 02:41:56.040
[Amit Varma]: So has there been a similar sort of evolution

02:41:56.040 --> 02:41:58.040
[Amit Varma]: with the way that you look at life,

02:41:58.040 --> 02:42:00.040
[Amit Varma]: especially with parenthood and all?

02:42:00.040 --> 02:42:02.040
[Amit Varma]: Because I guess being a father then must make you

02:42:02.040 --> 02:42:04.040
[Amit Varma]: take that step back.

02:42:04.040 --> 02:42:06.040
[Amit Varma]: And you know, when you were young,

02:42:06.040 --> 02:42:08.040
[Amit Varma]: were there goals like, hey, I want to be, you know,

02:42:08.040 --> 02:42:10.040
[Amit Varma]: a world-famous guitarist or, you know,

02:42:10.040 --> 02:42:12.040
[Amit Varma]: Zero will be this big band or whatever.

02:42:12.040 --> 02:42:17.040
[Amit Varma]: And where you are today, you know,

02:42:17.040 --> 02:42:19.040
[Amit Varma]: what do you think of as making you happy

02:42:19.040 --> 02:42:21.040
[Amit Varma]: over the next 5 years, 10 years, 15 years?

02:42:21.040 --> 02:42:23.040
[Amit Varma]: Is it just doing the stuff that you love

02:42:23.040 --> 02:42:25.040
[Amit Varma]: without thinking about what comes out of it?

02:42:25.040 --> 02:42:27.040
[Amit Varma]: Or is it that, no, there are these things

02:42:27.040 --> 02:42:30.040
[Amit Varma]: that I also want to kind of figure out?

02:42:30.040 --> 02:42:34.040
[Guest]: I'll tell you about like goals when I was much younger,

02:42:34.040 --> 02:42:36.040
[Guest]: like around the time I was 17 or 18.

02:42:36.040 --> 02:42:39.040
[Guest]: I wanted to play Rang Bhavan.

02:42:39.040 --> 02:42:42.040
[Guest]: I wanted to get stoned with my friends.

02:42:42.040 --> 02:42:44.040
[Guest]: And I wanted to have a girlfriend.

02:42:44.040 --> 02:42:45.040
[Guest]: So by the time I was 18,

02:42:45.040 --> 02:42:48.040
[Guest]: all those three things had been accomplished.

02:42:48.040 --> 02:42:51.040
[Guest]: So I was, you know, onto a good streak there.

02:42:51.040 --> 02:42:54.040
[Guest]: Then things started happening with the band and everything.

02:42:54.040 --> 02:42:56.040
[Guest]: And, you know, like after Rang Bhavan was the next thing,

02:42:56.040 --> 02:43:00.040
[Guest]: like I said, we did the great Indian rock thing.

02:43:00.040 --> 02:43:04.040
[Guest]: But by the time I think I reached around 30 or so,

02:43:04.040 --> 02:43:06.040
[Guest]: then I figured, you know,

02:43:06.040 --> 02:43:08.040
[Guest]: actually the whole process of, I mean,

02:43:08.040 --> 02:43:11.040
[Guest]: the whole journey is as important,

02:43:11.040 --> 02:43:15.040
[Guest]: if not more important than the goals you achieve.

02:43:15.040 --> 02:43:16.040
[Guest]: So in that sense, I've never really been

02:43:16.040 --> 02:43:18.040
[Guest]: the most ambitious person, you know,

02:43:18.040 --> 02:43:20.040
[Guest]: like I want to play Madison Square Garden.

02:43:20.040 --> 02:43:22.040
[Guest]: I was pretty, like, realistic.

02:43:22.040 --> 02:43:24.040
[Guest]: Like, Rang Bhavan's a good, you know,

02:43:24.040 --> 02:43:26.040
[Guest]: and Rang Bhavan is as good as Madison Square Garden

02:43:26.040 --> 02:43:27.040
[Guest]: for me personally.

02:43:27.040 --> 02:43:30.040
[Guest]: Like, that venue's got, like, plenty of history

02:43:30.040 --> 02:43:32.040
[Guest]: and vibe and everything like that.

02:43:32.040 --> 02:43:35.040
[Guest]: You know, so in terms of, like,

02:43:35.040 --> 02:43:38.040
[Guest]: also having a music accepted,

02:43:38.040 --> 02:43:41.040
[Guest]: how many listeners is enough, you know?

02:43:41.040 --> 02:43:43.040
[Guest]: Once you get to a point, like,

02:43:43.040 --> 02:43:45.040
[Guest]: if you get to a point where your Spotify streams,

02:43:45.040 --> 02:43:50.040
[Guest]: I mean, your streaming payments can support your lifestyle,

02:43:50.040 --> 02:43:52.040
[Guest]: that's great, you know,

02:43:52.040 --> 02:43:54.040
[Guest]: but you need so many of those,

02:43:54.040 --> 02:43:57.040
[Guest]: which means making totally different choices,

02:43:57.040 --> 02:44:00.040
[Guest]: which, you know, for whatever reason

02:44:00.040 --> 02:44:04.040
[Guest]: is not something I want to do right now.

02:44:04.040 --> 02:44:07.040
[Guest]: If for whatever reason suddenly it becomes popular,

02:44:07.040 --> 02:44:08.040
[Guest]: I'm not going to, like, say, hey,

02:44:08.040 --> 02:44:10.040
[Guest]: no, keep it only to, like, you know,

02:44:10.040 --> 02:44:11.040
[Guest]: hardcore listeners.

02:44:11.040 --> 02:44:12.040
[Unknown]: Who wants to listen to it?

02:44:12.040 --> 02:44:13.040
[Guest]: Let them listen to it.

02:44:13.040 --> 02:44:15.040
[Guest]: So in that sense of, like, numbers and everything,

02:44:15.040 --> 02:44:17.040
[Guest]: I've never been able to play that game

02:44:17.040 --> 02:44:19.040
[Guest]: without having a bit of a laugh

02:44:19.040 --> 02:44:21.040
[Guest]: about, you know, how ridiculous the whole thing is.

02:44:21.040 --> 02:44:24.040
[Guest]: I mean, what really matters at the end of the day?

02:44:24.040 --> 02:44:28.040
[Guest]: You know, like, just genuine enjoyment from the music

02:44:28.040 --> 02:44:31.040
[Guest]: and while making it and while listening to it.

02:44:31.040 --> 02:44:33.040
[Guest]: You know, I mean, if you can reduce it down,

02:44:33.040 --> 02:44:34.040
[Guest]: I've always been that, like,

02:44:34.040 --> 02:44:35.040
[Guest]: let's reduce it to, like,

02:44:35.040 --> 02:44:37.040
[Guest]: the simplest thing that it could be

02:44:37.040 --> 02:44:39.040
[Guest]: and find some enjoyment in that,

02:44:39.040 --> 02:44:40.040
[Guest]: and then, you know,

02:44:40.040 --> 02:44:43.040
[Guest]: the other things tend to take care of themselves.

02:44:43.040 --> 02:44:46.040
[Guest]: So in terms of goals,

02:44:46.040 --> 02:44:47.040
[Guest]: I guess, like, just, you know,

02:44:47.040 --> 02:44:50.040
[Guest]: keeping a roof over the family's head is, like,

02:44:50.040 --> 02:44:53.040
[Guest]: you know, the main thing right now.

02:44:53.040 --> 02:44:54.040
[Guest]: And if we can, you know,

02:44:54.040 --> 02:44:57.040
[Guest]: make some good music while doing that,

02:44:57.040 --> 02:44:58.040
[Guest]: then that's, you know,

02:44:58.040 --> 02:45:01.040
[Guest]: you want to keep us alive in the creative

02:45:01.040 --> 02:45:04.040
[Guest]: and spiritual sense.

02:45:04.040 --> 02:45:06.040
[Guest]: And also, like,

02:45:06.040 --> 02:45:10.040
[Guest]: finding as many different kinds of music to appreciate,

02:45:10.040 --> 02:45:11.040
[Guest]: you know, because life is short.

02:45:11.040 --> 02:45:13.040
[Guest]: You're never going to get to the bottom of it.

02:45:13.040 --> 02:45:15.040
[Guest]: You're never going to find the magic cord

02:45:15.040 --> 02:45:17.040
[Guest]: or, you know, whatever it is.

02:45:17.040 --> 02:45:20.040
[Guest]: So I just like finding pieces.

02:45:20.040 --> 02:45:22.040
[Guest]: The thing is, when I find music

02:45:22.040 --> 02:45:23.040
[Guest]: that I don't know how it's done,

02:45:23.040 --> 02:45:24.040
[Guest]: where I don't know the formula,

02:45:24.040 --> 02:45:26.040
[Guest]: I don't know the magic trick behind it,

02:45:26.040 --> 02:45:27.040
[Guest]: I appreciate that more

02:45:27.040 --> 02:45:28.040
[Guest]: because then it becomes, like,

02:45:28.040 --> 02:45:30.040
[Guest]: a very, like, you know,

02:45:30.040 --> 02:45:32.040
[Guest]: I just enjoy it for its sake.

02:45:32.040 --> 02:45:33.040
[Guest]: The moment I know,

02:45:33.040 --> 02:45:35.040
[Guest]: okay, this is the formula,

02:45:35.040 --> 02:45:36.040
[Guest]: I was like,

02:45:36.040 --> 02:45:37.040
[Guest]: this is, like, you know,

02:45:37.040 --> 02:45:39.040
[Guest]: leave it for someone else to enjoy this.

02:45:39.040 --> 02:45:40.040
[Guest]: But there's still, like,

02:45:40.040 --> 02:45:42.040
[Guest]: a lot of pop music I still love,

02:45:42.040 --> 02:45:44.040
[Guest]: like Def Leppard or White Snake.

02:45:44.040 --> 02:45:45.040
[Guest]: And you can, like,

02:45:45.040 --> 02:45:47.040
[Guest]: you can read the producers telling you,

02:45:47.040 --> 02:45:49.040
[Guest]: okay, this is why we, you know,

02:45:49.040 --> 02:45:51.040
[Guest]: made so-and-so creative decision,

02:45:51.040 --> 02:45:54.040
[Guest]: which is not exactly the most musical one or whatever.

02:45:54.040 --> 02:45:55.040
[Guest]: It still works, you know,

02:45:55.040 --> 02:45:57.040
[Guest]: because that's something I guess you enjoy

02:45:57.040 --> 02:45:58.040
[Guest]: when you were younger

02:45:58.040 --> 02:46:00.040
[Guest]: and you didn't have those, you know,

02:46:00.040 --> 02:46:04.040
[Guest]: judgmental, you know, faculties about you.

02:46:04.040 --> 02:46:06.040
[Guest]: So, you know, again,

02:46:06.040 --> 02:46:08.040
[Unknown]: who's to say what is real?

02:46:08.040 --> 02:46:09.040
[Unknown]: Yeah.

02:46:09.040 --> 02:46:14.040
[Guest]: The realest you can get is

02:46:14.040 --> 02:46:18.040
[Guest]: when you're able to put in something

02:46:18.040 --> 02:46:20.040
[Guest]: that is honest

02:46:20.040 --> 02:46:23.040
[Guest]: and the listener is able to perceive

02:46:23.040 --> 02:46:25.040
[Guest]: that honesty and that authenticity

02:46:25.040 --> 02:46:27.040
[Guest]: or whatever you want to call it.

02:46:27.040 --> 02:46:29.040
[Guest]: For me, then, at least,

02:46:29.040 --> 02:46:33.040
[Guest]: that's the first thing taken care of, you know.

02:46:33.040 --> 02:46:34.040
[Guest]: Then you see later, like,

02:46:34.040 --> 02:46:36.040
[Guest]: where we're going to play,

02:46:36.040 --> 02:46:37.040
[Guest]: what kind of gigs we're going to do,

02:46:37.040 --> 02:46:38.040
[Guest]: what's the backstage rider,

02:46:38.040 --> 02:46:40.040
[Guest]: like all that will come later.

02:46:40.040 --> 02:46:42.040
[Guest]: Another guy who I've always appreciated

02:46:42.040 --> 02:46:44.040
[Guest]: for who, you know,

02:46:44.040 --> 02:46:46.040
[Guest]: is able to do that as well as Taj,

02:46:46.040 --> 02:46:47.040
[Guest]: Tajdar Junaid.

02:46:47.040 --> 02:46:50.040
[Guest]: He's always done exactly what he wanted to do

02:46:50.040 --> 02:46:51.040
[Guest]: and, you know,

02:46:51.040 --> 02:46:53.040
[Guest]: you can sense that in his music.

02:46:53.040 --> 02:46:54.040
[Guest]: So, like, another,

02:46:54.040 --> 02:46:56.040
[Guest]: it's almost like we've had, like,

02:46:56.040 --> 02:46:57.040
[Guest]: parallel careers.

02:46:57.040 --> 02:46:59.040
[Guest]: And now one of the things he's done,

02:46:59.040 --> 02:47:01.040
[Guest]: went in for an Oscar nomination,

02:47:01.040 --> 02:47:03.040
[Guest]: which is damn amazing, you know,

02:47:03.040 --> 02:47:05.040
[Guest]: like super happy for him right now.

02:47:05.040 --> 02:47:07.040
[Amit Varma]: I was just listening to his track,

02:47:07.040 --> 02:47:08.040
[Amit Varma]: Color is Your Raindrop yesterday,

02:47:08.040 --> 02:47:09.040
[Amit Varma]: beautiful track.

02:47:09.040 --> 02:47:12.040
[Amit Varma]: And somehow it reminded me of a similar vibe

02:47:12.040 --> 02:47:13.040
[Amit Varma]: to Ode to a Sunny Day.

02:47:13.040 --> 02:47:15.040
[Amit Varma]: You know, I just kind of heard them back to back

02:47:15.040 --> 02:47:16.040
[Amit Varma]: and it just, you know,

02:47:16.040 --> 02:47:18.040
[Amit Varma]: both of them are just so soothing

02:47:18.040 --> 02:47:20.040
[Amit Varma]: and so kind of wonderful.

02:47:20.040 --> 02:47:23.040
[Amit Varma]: And when I was watching his video for Dastan,

02:47:23.040 --> 02:47:25.040
[Amit Varma]: somebody left an interesting comment.

02:47:25.040 --> 02:47:29.040
[Amit Varma]: They said that every time they reach to 15,

02:47:29.040 --> 02:47:30.040
[Amit Varma]: two minutes, 15 seconds in the song,

02:47:30.040 --> 02:47:31.040
[Amit Varma]: they start crying.

02:47:31.040 --> 02:47:32.040
[Amit Varma]: And then below that,

02:47:32.040 --> 02:47:34.040
[Amit Varma]: someone else left a comment saying that,

02:47:34.040 --> 02:47:35.040
[Amit Varma]: why do you start crying?

02:47:35.040 --> 02:47:37.040
[Amit Varma]: And, you know, it's just a song.

02:47:37.040 --> 02:47:39.040
[Amit Varma]: And then somebody else came and said that,

02:47:39.040 --> 02:47:41.040
[Amit Varma]: no, it's not a song, it's a story, right?

02:47:41.040 --> 02:47:43.040
[Amit Varma]: And every time I reached that part of the story,

02:47:43.040 --> 02:47:44.040
[Amit Varma]: I know what's coming,

02:47:44.040 --> 02:47:45.040
[Amit Varma]: but I can't help myself.

02:47:45.040 --> 02:47:47.040
[Amit Varma]: And I just thought that that is

02:47:47.040 --> 02:47:48.040
[Amit Varma]: such a beautiful sentiment.

02:47:48.040 --> 02:47:51.040
[Amit Varma]: And sometimes if you listen to music

02:47:51.040 --> 02:47:52.040
[Amit Varma]: and I have to keep reminding myself

02:47:52.040 --> 02:47:54.040
[Amit Varma]: to be more mindful in all the things I do,

02:47:54.040 --> 02:47:55.040
[Amit Varma]: not just music,

02:47:55.040 --> 02:47:57.040
[Amit Varma]: but sometimes when you listen to music like that,

02:47:57.040 --> 02:47:59.040
[Amit Varma]: that magical thing can happen

02:47:59.040 --> 02:48:01.040
[Amit Varma]: where you feel you're going on a journey

02:48:01.040 --> 02:48:02.040
[Amit Varma]: through the song and so on.

02:48:02.040 --> 02:48:04.040
[Amit Varma]: So when you sort of write your music,

02:48:04.040 --> 02:48:06.040
[Amit Varma]: do you also feel that,

02:48:06.040 --> 02:48:08.040
[Amit Varma]: sure, there are no vocals,

02:48:08.040 --> 02:48:10.040
[Amit Varma]: you're just building a soundscape,

02:48:10.040 --> 02:48:11.040
[Amit Varma]: you're playing your guitar,

02:48:11.040 --> 02:48:12.040
[Amit Varma]: you're doing your thing,

02:48:12.040 --> 02:48:13.040
[Amit Varma]: but there is a story,

02:48:13.040 --> 02:48:14.040
[Amit Varma]: there is a progression.

02:48:14.040 --> 02:48:15.040
[Amit Varma]: Do you also feel that?

02:48:15.040 --> 02:48:17.040
[Amit Varma]: Does your own music move you sometimes?

02:48:17.040 --> 02:48:19.040
[Guest]: Yeah, it has to actually,

02:48:19.040 --> 02:48:20.040
[Guest]: at some point in the process.

02:48:20.040 --> 02:48:24.040
[Guest]: Otherwise, you know, it gets scrapped.

02:48:24.040 --> 02:48:25.040
[Guest]: At some point,

02:48:25.040 --> 02:48:27.040
[Guest]: I have to get like the chills.

02:48:27.040 --> 02:48:28.040
[Guest]: I mean, it won't happen again

02:48:28.040 --> 02:48:30.040
[Guest]: and every single time I listen to it.

02:48:30.040 --> 02:48:32.040
[Guest]: But I mean, at one point,

02:48:32.040 --> 02:48:34.040
[Guest]: like ode to a sunny day was my music

02:48:34.040 --> 02:48:36.040
[Guest]: that I listened to to fall asleep,

02:48:36.040 --> 02:48:37.040
[Guest]: you know, for like a good month

02:48:37.040 --> 02:48:38.040
[Guest]: or a couple of months.

02:48:38.040 --> 02:48:40.040
[Guest]: I just put it on every night while going to sleep.

02:48:40.040 --> 02:48:42.040
[Guest]: Otherwise, like my head was full of too much stuff

02:48:42.040 --> 02:48:44.040
[Guest]: that, you know, kept you awake.

02:48:44.040 --> 02:48:46.040
[Guest]: So that was the thing that kind of, you know,

02:48:46.040 --> 02:48:48.040
[Guest]: soothed those beasts in your head

02:48:48.040 --> 02:48:50.040
[Guest]: and say, okay, it's okay, now go to sleep.

02:48:50.040 --> 02:48:52.040
[Guest]: So if it has that effect on you,

02:48:52.040 --> 02:48:54.040
[Guest]: like I said, it's a good chance

02:48:54.040 --> 02:48:58.040
[Guest]: it'll have that effect on someone else.

02:48:58.040 --> 02:49:00.040
[Guest]: And there's also things like sometimes

02:49:00.040 --> 02:49:02.040
[Guest]: you take for granted that you do it

02:49:02.040 --> 02:49:03.040
[Guest]: and it just happens.

02:49:03.040 --> 02:49:04.040
[Guest]: And then someone else will say,

02:49:04.040 --> 02:49:05.040
[Guest]: oh, wow, that's amazing.

02:49:05.040 --> 02:49:07.040
[Guest]: I was like, oh, you like that?

02:49:07.040 --> 02:49:09.040
[Guest]: And there's sometimes like where you think like,

02:49:09.040 --> 02:49:11.040
[Guest]: wow, how clever I am, you know,

02:49:11.040 --> 02:49:12.040
[Guest]: and no one gets it.

02:49:12.040 --> 02:49:14.040
[Guest]: You know, it just flies over everyone else.

02:49:14.040 --> 02:49:16.040
[Guest]: And then like not one person

02:49:16.040 --> 02:49:17.040
[Guest]: will bring it up or whatever.

02:49:17.040 --> 02:49:19.040
[Guest]: So there's been a few of those,

02:49:19.040 --> 02:49:20.040
[Guest]: but you never know,

02:49:20.040 --> 02:49:21.040
[Guest]: maybe like 20 years later,

02:49:21.040 --> 02:49:22.040
[Guest]: someone will say, hey, what about,

02:49:22.040 --> 02:49:24.040
[Guest]: you know, that little thing?

02:49:24.040 --> 02:49:26.040
[Guest]: Like on the zero sounds,

02:49:26.040 --> 02:49:29.040
[Guest]: I'll be like, yeah, someone finally got it.

02:49:29.040 --> 02:49:32.040
[Amit Varma]: So, you know, as we wrap up

02:49:32.040 --> 02:49:33.040
[Amit Varma]: a couple of final questions,

02:49:33.040 --> 02:49:36.040
[Amit Varma]: and one is if there are young musicians

02:49:36.040 --> 02:49:37.040
[Amit Varma]: listening to this,

02:49:37.040 --> 02:49:39.040
[Amit Varma]: and obviously it's challenging in India

02:49:39.040 --> 02:49:40.040
[Amit Varma]: or anywhere, I guess,

02:49:40.040 --> 02:49:41.040
[Amit Varma]: to be a young musician

02:49:41.040 --> 02:49:42.040
[Amit Varma]: because you don't know

02:49:42.040 --> 02:49:43.040
[Amit Varma]: where the money is going to come from.

02:49:43.040 --> 02:49:45.040
[Amit Varma]: You've always got to sort of

02:49:45.040 --> 02:49:46.040
[Amit Varma]: find that fine balance

02:49:46.040 --> 02:49:47.040
[Amit Varma]: between doing what you love

02:49:47.040 --> 02:49:49.040
[Amit Varma]: and just having to make a living, right?

02:49:49.040 --> 02:49:52.040
[Amit Varma]: And what advice would you give them?

02:49:52.040 --> 02:49:54.040
[Amit Varma]: And I mean, in a general broad sense,

02:49:54.040 --> 02:49:55.040
[Amit Varma]: not just career advice

02:49:55.040 --> 02:49:57.040
[Amit Varma]: in terms of making money or making music,

02:49:57.040 --> 02:49:58.040
[Amit Varma]: but even learning music,

02:49:58.040 --> 02:49:59.040
[Amit Varma]: appreciating music.

02:49:59.040 --> 02:50:00.040
[Amit Varma]: Like if you were to meet,

02:50:00.040 --> 02:50:02.040
[Amit Varma]: say the 18 year old

02:50:02.040 --> 02:50:03.040
[Amit Varma]: or the 17 year old

02:50:03.040 --> 02:50:04.040
[Amit Varma]: before your three goals come true,

02:50:04.040 --> 02:50:05.040
[Amit Varma]: if you were to meet

02:50:05.040 --> 02:50:07.040
[Amit Varma]: the 17 year old Warren today,

02:50:07.040 --> 02:50:10.040
[Amit Varma]: what advice would you give him?

02:50:10.040 --> 02:50:12.040
[Guest]: In fact, I just put out a video today

02:50:12.040 --> 02:50:14.040
[Guest]: saying like 10 things I wish I had.

02:50:14.040 --> 02:50:16.040
[Guest]: We'll link it from the show notes.

02:50:16.040 --> 02:50:18.040
[Guest]: Some of it is a bit technical

02:50:18.040 --> 02:50:20.040
[Guest]: because like there were musical discoveries

02:50:20.040 --> 02:50:21.040
[Guest]: that happened like much later,

02:50:21.040 --> 02:50:24.040
[Guest]: which I wish had been communicated to me.

02:50:24.040 --> 02:50:27.040
[Guest]: Somebody should have told me that.

02:50:27.040 --> 02:50:29.040
[Guest]: Generally, I would say

02:50:29.040 --> 02:50:32.040
[Guest]: keep your enjoyment of music sacrosanct.

02:50:32.040 --> 02:50:33.040
[Guest]: Never get to a point

02:50:33.040 --> 02:50:35.040
[Guest]: where it just becomes a drudgery

02:50:35.040 --> 02:50:36.040
[Guest]: because then you've got to check out

02:50:36.040 --> 02:50:37.040
[Guest]: at that point

02:50:37.040 --> 02:50:38.040
[Guest]: and do something else for a while

02:50:38.040 --> 02:50:39.040
[Guest]: and then maybe come back to it.

02:50:39.040 --> 02:50:41.040
[Guest]: So if it gets to that point,

02:50:41.040 --> 02:50:44.040
[Guest]: you're doing something wrong.

02:50:44.040 --> 02:50:47.040
[Guest]: Try to play with

02:50:47.040 --> 02:50:49.040
[Guest]: as many good musicians

02:50:49.040 --> 02:50:50.040
[Guest]: you can as possible.

02:50:50.040 --> 02:50:53.040
[Guest]: Like I think like my best growth spot

02:50:53.040 --> 02:50:54.040
[Guest]: as a musician happened at this time

02:50:54.040 --> 02:50:55.040
[Guest]: when I was playing with Cole

02:50:55.040 --> 02:50:57.040
[Guest]: and a couple of his friends

02:50:57.040 --> 02:50:59.040
[Guest]: in this covers band every Friday night.

02:50:59.040 --> 02:51:01.040
[Guest]: And it's brutal.

02:51:01.040 --> 02:51:03.040
[Guest]: I mean, you go through that process

02:51:03.040 --> 02:51:05.040
[Guest]: of just playing like what's popular

02:51:05.040 --> 02:51:06.040
[Guest]: at that point of time,

02:51:06.040 --> 02:51:07.040
[Guest]: but you try to do it in a way

02:51:07.040 --> 02:51:09.040
[Guest]: which like you yourself are feeling it.

02:51:09.040 --> 02:51:11.040
[Guest]: Otherwise, people are not going to

02:51:11.040 --> 02:51:12.040
[Guest]: react on that.

02:51:12.040 --> 02:51:15.040
[Guest]: So when you're the worst guy in a band,

02:51:15.040 --> 02:51:17.040
[Guest]: that's probably like the best position

02:51:17.040 --> 02:51:18.040
[Guest]: you can be in.

02:51:18.040 --> 02:51:19.040
[Guest]: If you think you're like

02:51:19.040 --> 02:51:21.040
[Guest]: the shit hot guy in the band,

02:51:21.040 --> 02:51:22.040
[Guest]: leave the band, right?

02:51:22.040 --> 02:51:24.040
[Guest]: Then find some better guys to play with.

02:51:24.040 --> 02:51:26.040
[Guest]: I mean, it sounds easier said than done,

02:51:26.040 --> 02:51:28.040
[Guest]: but you kind of have to

02:51:28.040 --> 02:51:31.040
[Guest]: get to that process.

02:51:31.040 --> 02:51:33.040
[Guest]: And I mean, keep an eye on the money.

02:51:33.040 --> 02:51:34.040
[Guest]: You may know where your bills

02:51:34.040 --> 02:51:35.040
[Guest]: are being paid and stuff like that.

02:51:35.040 --> 02:51:37.040
[Guest]: Don't be that, you know,

02:51:37.040 --> 02:51:38.040
[Guest]: I'm only going to do it

02:51:38.040 --> 02:51:39.040
[Guest]: for art's sake and everything.

02:51:39.040 --> 02:51:41.040
[Guest]: You have to obviously make sure

02:51:41.040 --> 02:51:45.040
[Guest]: your financial things are met.

02:51:45.040 --> 02:51:48.040
[Guest]: But you can always find a balance.

02:51:48.040 --> 02:51:50.040
[Guest]: Finding a balance sometimes is tricky,

02:51:50.040 --> 02:51:52.040
[Guest]: but that's what I've been doing.

02:51:52.040 --> 02:51:54.040
[Guest]: I've just been juggling both ends

02:51:54.040 --> 02:51:58.040
[Guest]: of the thing, trying to keep afloat.

02:51:58.040 --> 02:52:00.040
[Guest]: Don't really focus only on one

02:52:00.040 --> 02:52:01.040
[Guest]: genre of music.

02:52:01.040 --> 02:52:03.040
[Guest]: Try to steal from as many different

02:52:03.040 --> 02:52:04.040
[Guest]: people as you can,

02:52:04.040 --> 02:52:06.040
[Guest]: because then no one will know you're stealing.

02:52:06.040 --> 02:52:07.040
[Guest]: If you steal from one person,

02:52:07.040 --> 02:52:08.040
[Guest]: everyone's going to notice,

02:52:08.040 --> 02:52:10.040
[Guest]: that's where you got all your shit from.

02:52:10.040 --> 02:52:12.040
[Guest]: So take a little bit, little bit, little bit,

02:52:12.040 --> 02:52:13.040
[Guest]: then no one will really notice

02:52:13.040 --> 02:52:16.040
[Guest]: where you got your stuff from.

02:52:16.040 --> 02:52:19.040
[Guest]: And the thing is to kind of

02:52:19.040 --> 02:52:21.040
[Guest]: develop a certain amount of confidence

02:52:21.040 --> 02:52:22.040
[Guest]: in what you do.

02:52:22.040 --> 02:52:23.040
[Guest]: Otherwise, it's never going to

02:52:23.040 --> 02:52:24.040
[Guest]: get past that point.

02:52:24.040 --> 02:52:26.040
[Guest]: If you're always second-guessing yourself,

02:52:26.040 --> 02:52:27.040
[Guest]: you're never going to get to a point,

02:52:27.040 --> 02:52:29.040
[Guest]: like I bet all your favorite artists

02:52:29.040 --> 02:52:31.040
[Guest]: had some amount of confidence

02:52:31.040 --> 02:52:32.040
[Guest]: in what they were doing,

02:52:32.040 --> 02:52:34.040
[Guest]: which enabled them to just put it out,

02:52:34.040 --> 02:52:35.040
[Guest]: you know, and do whatever it is

02:52:35.040 --> 02:52:36.040
[Guest]: that they're doing.

02:52:36.040 --> 02:52:38.040
[Unknown]: Yeah.

02:52:38.040 --> 02:52:41.040
[Unknown]: Just an observation on this.

02:52:41.040 --> 02:52:42.040
[Unknown]: To me, in many ways,

02:52:42.040 --> 02:52:44.040
[Unknown]: it's kind of surreal being part

02:52:44.040 --> 02:52:46.040
[Unknown]: of this recording as,

02:52:46.040 --> 02:52:48.040
[Unknown]: you know, a fan of your music for so long.

02:52:48.040 --> 02:52:50.040
[Unknown]: This, and this might seem kind of cheesy,

02:52:50.040 --> 02:52:52.040
[Unknown]: but this entire recording itself

02:52:52.040 --> 02:52:53.040
[Unknown]: felt like a Blackstripe Blues song

02:52:53.040 --> 02:52:55.040
[Unknown]: in much the same way

02:52:55.040 --> 02:52:57.040
[Unknown]: that you read out that quote

02:52:57.040 --> 02:52:58.040
[Unknown]: of my own that I wrote.

02:52:58.040 --> 02:53:01.040
[Unknown]: It started off with the nice punchy bits,

02:53:01.040 --> 02:53:02.040
[Unknown]: and then it moved into

02:53:02.040 --> 02:53:03.040
[Unknown]: a slightly poignant part.

02:53:03.040 --> 02:53:04.040
[Unknown]: And then towards the end,

02:53:04.040 --> 02:53:05.040
[Unknown]: there was the emotional guitar solo

02:53:05.040 --> 02:53:07.040
[Unknown]: when you were talking about all this.

02:53:07.040 --> 02:53:09.040
[Unknown]: And now it's ending on the crescendo again.

02:53:09.040 --> 02:53:10.040
[Unknown]: So I know it's a cheesy way

02:53:10.040 --> 02:53:11.040
[Unknown]: of tying it all back in,

02:53:11.040 --> 02:53:13.040
[Unknown]: but that to me is the observation

02:53:13.040 --> 02:53:15.040
[Unknown]: of this entire conversation itself.

02:53:15.040 --> 02:53:16.040
[Unknown]: And it was like a perfect

02:53:16.040 --> 02:53:19.040
[Unknown]: Blackstripe Blues interview in some sense.

02:53:19.040 --> 02:53:21.040
[Unknown]: So yeah, that's the observation that I have.

02:53:21.040 --> 02:53:22.040
[Unknown]: It's not really a question.

02:53:22.040 --> 02:53:25.040
[Unknown]: I don't have anything else to ask on this.

02:53:25.040 --> 02:53:27.040
[Unknown]: As long as it works.

02:53:27.040 --> 02:53:29.040
[Amit Varma]: Yeah, exactly.

02:53:29.040 --> 02:53:31.040
[Amit Varma]: I mean, to compare a session I've done

02:53:31.040 --> 02:53:32.040
[Amit Varma]: with a Blackstripe Blues song

02:53:32.040 --> 02:53:33.040
[Amit Varma]: is a great compliment,

02:53:33.040 --> 02:53:34.040
[Amit Varma]: but I'll take time to process

02:53:34.040 --> 02:53:35.040
[Amit Varma]: exactly what you meant.

02:53:35.040 --> 02:53:38.040
[Amit Varma]: But since you want to end on a crescendo,

02:53:38.040 --> 02:53:39.040
[Amit Varma]: we can end on a crescendo

02:53:39.040 --> 02:53:40.040
[Amit Varma]: because this is often the favorite part

02:53:40.040 --> 02:53:41.040
[Amit Varma]: of the show for many people,

02:53:41.040 --> 02:53:43.040
[Amit Varma]: which is in general,

02:53:43.040 --> 02:53:45.040
[Amit Varma]: I ask my guests to recommend books

02:53:45.040 --> 02:53:46.040
[Amit Varma]: or films or music,

02:53:46.040 --> 02:53:47.040
[Amit Varma]: which they absolutely love

02:53:47.040 --> 02:53:48.040
[Amit Varma]: and they want to share with the world.

02:53:48.040 --> 02:53:49.040
[Amit Varma]: In your case,

02:53:49.040 --> 02:53:50.040
[Amit Varma]: I guess it'll mainly be music,

02:53:50.040 --> 02:53:52.040
[Amit Varma]: but whatever else you want to recommend.

02:53:52.040 --> 02:53:53.040
[Amit Varma]: But in the sense,

02:53:53.040 --> 02:53:55.040
[Amit Varma]: stuff that you're so excited about

02:53:55.040 --> 02:53:57.040
[Amit Varma]: that you want to stand on a soapbox

02:53:57.040 --> 02:53:58.040
[Amit Varma]: and shout at the world,

02:53:58.040 --> 02:53:59.040
[Amit Varma]: Hey, listen to this.

02:53:59.040 --> 02:54:02.040
[Amit Varma]: This is amazing.

02:54:02.040 --> 02:54:05.040
[Guest]: I mean, I guess everyone's seen Spinal Tap.

02:54:05.040 --> 02:54:06.040
[Guest]: If you haven't, please check it out.

02:54:06.040 --> 02:54:09.040
[Guest]: That's like one of my favorite films.

02:54:09.040 --> 02:54:11.040
[Guest]: All the Monty Python stuff I love,

02:54:11.040 --> 02:54:14.040
[Guest]: especially I think people these days

02:54:14.040 --> 02:54:17.040
[Guest]: who have problems with religion

