[Amit Varma]: He's been on my show,

02:54:42.040 --> 02:54:43.040
[Amit Varma]: Krish Ashok.

02:54:43.040 --> 02:54:44.040
[Amit Varma]: We had a three-hour episode

02:54:44.040 --> 02:54:45.040
[Amit Varma]: and he's a fine musician,

02:54:45.040 --> 02:54:46.040
[Amit Varma]: by the way,

02:54:46.040 --> 02:54:48.040
[Amit Varma]: you should check out some of his music.

02:54:48.040 --> 02:54:49.040
[Amit Varma]: He does incredible,

02:54:49.040 --> 02:54:52.040
[Amit Varma]: like he'll take a famous Western song

02:54:52.040 --> 02:54:53.040
[Amit Varma]: or a piece of opera

02:54:53.040 --> 02:54:54.040
[Amit Varma]: and convert it to Carnatic

02:54:54.040 --> 02:54:56.040
[Amit Varma]: and he'll do his things with it.

02:54:56.040 --> 02:54:57.040
[Amit Varma]: So I think you'll love him.

02:54:57.040 --> 02:54:58.040
[Guest]: Yeah, you should check him out.

02:54:58.040 --> 02:54:59.040
[Guest]: I will check out his music.

02:54:59.040 --> 02:55:01.040
[Guest]: There's an account on YouTube

02:55:01.040 --> 02:55:03.040
[Guest]: I found called Bill McClintock

02:55:03.040 --> 02:55:05.040
[Guest]: who does some amazing mashups

02:55:05.040 --> 02:55:06.040
[Guest]: like his specialities,

02:55:06.040 --> 02:55:08.040
[Guest]: taking like 80s metal

02:55:08.040 --> 02:55:10.040
[Guest]: and mashing it up with 70s R&B,

02:55:10.040 --> 02:55:12.040
[Guest]: which, you know, you'll find some.

02:55:12.040 --> 02:55:13.040
[Guest]: There's one with Aerosmith,

02:55:13.040 --> 02:55:15.040
[Guest]: Sweet Emotion and Aretha Franklin,

02:55:15.040 --> 02:55:16.040
[Guest]: which is like amazing.

02:55:16.040 --> 02:55:17.040
[Guest]: It kind of gave me a little

02:55:17.040 --> 02:55:18.040
[Guest]: of the goosebumps

02:55:18.040 --> 02:55:21.040
[Guest]: when Aretha kicked into the chorus,

02:55:21.040 --> 02:55:22.040
[Guest]: which, you know,

02:55:22.040 --> 02:55:23.040
[Guest]: you get in any case.

02:55:23.040 --> 02:55:25.040
[Guest]: If you haven't heard Derek Trucks,

02:55:25.040 --> 02:55:26.040
[Guest]: please check him out.

02:55:26.040 --> 02:55:28.040
[Guest]: If you haven't heard Michael Landau,

02:55:28.040 --> 02:55:29.040
[Guest]: please check him out.

02:55:29.040 --> 02:55:31.040
[Guest]: He's like if Hendrix learned

02:55:31.040 --> 02:55:33.040
[Guest]: a bit more jazz

02:55:33.040 --> 02:55:35.040
[Guest]: and kind of got like

02:55:35.040 --> 02:55:37.040
[Guest]: a more polished guitar sound.

02:55:37.040 --> 02:55:39.040
[Guest]: If you haven't heard Jeff Beck

02:55:39.040 --> 02:55:41.040
[Guest]: doing Nithin Soni's Nadia,

02:55:41.040 --> 02:55:42.040
[Guest]: please check that out.

02:55:42.040 --> 02:55:43.040
[Guest]: That's one of the finest bits

02:55:43.040 --> 02:55:44.040
[Guest]: of guitar playing.

02:55:44.040 --> 02:55:45.040
[Guest]: There's another one he did

02:55:45.040 --> 02:55:47.040
[Guest]: called Where Were You,

02:55:47.040 --> 02:55:49.040
[Guest]: which I think is like

02:55:49.040 --> 02:55:50.040
[Guest]: one of the toughest things to play

02:55:50.040 --> 02:55:51.040
[Guest]: because he's playing melodies

02:55:51.040 --> 02:55:52.040
[Guest]: using the whammy bar

02:55:52.040 --> 02:55:53.040
[Guest]: and that thing is like

02:55:53.040 --> 02:55:55.040
[Guest]: notoriously tough to control

02:55:55.040 --> 02:55:57.040
[Guest]: exactly in pitch,

02:55:57.040 --> 02:55:58.040
[Guest]: but he manages to do it.

02:55:58.040 --> 02:56:00.040
[Guest]: So it's like these little bit of,

02:56:00.040 --> 02:56:02.040
[Guest]: you know, like the gods

02:56:02.040 --> 02:56:03.040
[Guest]: have visited us,

02:56:03.040 --> 02:56:04.040
[Guest]: you know, and that sort of thing.

02:56:04.040 --> 02:56:05.040
[Guest]: Again, like when I can't figure out

02:56:05.040 --> 02:56:06.040
[Guest]: how it's done,

02:56:06.040 --> 02:56:07.040
[Guest]: it just like,

02:56:07.040 --> 02:56:09.040
[Guest]: I can't figure out that magic trick

02:56:09.040 --> 02:56:11.040
[Guest]: which makes it like more incredible.

02:56:11.040 --> 02:56:12.040
[Guest]: That sort of thing.

02:56:12.040 --> 02:56:14.040
[Guest]: Apart from that,

02:56:16.040 --> 02:56:17.040
[Guest]: let me see.

02:56:17.040 --> 02:56:18.040
[Guest]: If you haven't heard

02:56:18.040 --> 02:56:19.040
[Guest]: Aranjoy Sarkar,

02:56:19.040 --> 02:56:20.040
[Guest]: he's one of the finest

02:56:20.040 --> 02:56:21.040
[Guest]: blues guitar players.

02:56:21.040 --> 02:56:22.040
[Guest]: That's what a blues guitar player does.

02:56:22.040 --> 02:56:23.040
[Guest]: I'm not a blues guitar player

02:56:23.040 --> 02:56:24.040
[Guest]: by any standard.

02:56:24.040 --> 02:56:25.040
[Guest]: I play the blues,

02:56:25.040 --> 02:56:26.040
[Guest]: but I'm not a blues man.

02:56:26.040 --> 02:56:28.040
[Guest]: So if you want to listen to

02:56:28.040 --> 02:56:30.040
[Guest]: authentic, bonafide

02:56:30.040 --> 02:56:32.040
[Guest]: blues guitar player,

02:56:32.040 --> 02:56:33.040
[Guest]: I'd say Aranjoy

02:56:33.040 --> 02:56:35.040
[Guest]: and Rudy Walang, of course.

02:56:35.040 --> 02:56:36.040
[Guest]: He's been keeping that style alive

02:56:36.040 --> 02:56:38.040
[Guest]: for years.

